=beginObject#instance_variable_set(from ~/.rdoc)------------------------------------------------------------------------------  obj.instance_variable_set(symbol, obj)    -> obj------------------------------------------------------------------------------Sets the instance variable names by symbol to object, there byfrustrating the efforts of the class's author to attempt to provide properencapsulation. The variable did not have to exist prior to this call.  class Fred    def initialize(p1, p2)      @a, @b = p1, p2    end  end  fred = Fred.new('cat', 99)  fred.instance_variable_set(:@a, 'dog')   #=> "dog"  fred.instance_variable_set(:@c, 'cat')   #=> "cat"  fred.inspect                             #=> "#<Fred:0x401b3da8 @a=\"dog\", @b=99, @c=\"cat\">"=end